The global sleeping medications market can be segmented based on various factors. Firstly, by product type, the market is categorized into prescription sleeping pills and over-the-counter (OTC) sleeping pills. Prescription sleeping pills require a doctor's approval before purchase, while OTC sleeping pills can be bought without a prescription. Secondly, based on sleep disorders, the market is divided into insomnia, sleep apnea, restless legs syndrome (RLS), narcolepsy, and others. Each disorder may require specific medications for treatment. Thirdly, concerning distribution channels, the market includes hospital pharmacies, retail pharmacies, and online pharmacies. Online pharmacies have gained popularity due to their convenience and accessibility. Lastly, geographically, the market is segmented into North America, Europe, Asia-Pacific, Latin America, and the Middle East and Africa, each region showing variations in market demand and growth.

